---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---
<BaseLayout
  title="About — Media Planning Jobs"
  description="Why Media Planning Jobs exists, and who runs it."
>
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-16 text-ink-700">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-semibold text-ink-900">About</h1>
    <p class="mt-4 text-lg">
      Media Planning Jobs is a specialist job board for media planners, buyers, ad operations, and programmatic professionals — the people who decide where billions of advertising dollars actually go.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-4">
      The big boards (Indeed, ZipRecruiter, LinkedIn) drown specialist roles in irrelevant volume. Generalist media boards (Mediabistro, Adweek Jobs) cover everything from journalism to creative. Neither is built for the media planning discipline.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-4">
      We're built by <a class="text-brand hover:underline" href="https://halliardmedia.com">Halliard</a>, the team behind <a class="text-brand hover:underline" href="https://mediaplanningtool.com">mediaplanningtool.com</a>. We've spent years building software for media planners — this is the hiring side of the same problem.
    </p>
    <h2 class="mt-10 text-xl font-semibold text-ink-900">For job seekers</h2>
    <p class="mt-2">Browse roles by function (planning, buying, ad ops, programmatic, analytics, strategy, leadership) and apply directly on the employer's site. No accounts, no resume gates.</p>
    <h2 class="mt-8 text-xl font-semibold text-ink-900">For employers</h2>
    <p class="mt-2"><a class="text-brand hover:underline" href="/post-a-job">Post a job</a> for $99 and reach the discipline directly. Listings are indexed in Google for Jobs and included in our weekly newsletter.</p>
    <h2 class="mt-8 text-xl font-semibold text-ink-900">Contact</h2>
    <p class="mt-2"><a class="text-brand hover:underline" href="mailto:hello@mediaplanningjobs.io">hello@mediaplanningjobs.io</a></p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
